Meet <b>Sean</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>Sean lives at <a href='/home/?user=hawkeyes'>15507 Castle Hill</a>, in the classy neighborhood of Westridge. He's lived there since September 1st, 2004, and just loves the wonderful view of Millsberry that he has from his house.<br><br>Our citizen of the week is a very caring and creative person, who enjoys hanging out at his friends' houses. They like to spend their time relaxing and reading comic books while listening to heavy metal or country music. What an interesting mix!<br><br>Sean is also very athletic, enjoying sports such as football and baseball. As you can tell from his impressive trophy collection, he is a young man of many talents! At Millsberry Academy, Sean has excelled in rope climbing, shooting hoops, and the always fun Hop and Drop competition.<br><br>He's also very bright, having earned himself both mathematical and spelling trophies, as well. He's even received a measure of appreciation from police chief Arthur Crow for all the civic duties that he's performed.<br><br>Another place where Sean likes to hang out is at the amusement park, where he and his friends can go on all sorts of rides and have a good time.<br><br>After a long day of playing sports and hanging out with his friends, Sean returns to his beautiful house, which he painted blue (since it happens to be his favorite color). Be sure to stop by Sean's house and introduce yourself sometime!</div>
